        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>July 31st 5625</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <add>Hebrew</add>
            </p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Michael Light</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>94 East Broadway</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                <date>July 31, 5625 (1865</date>).</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>,</p>
            <p>Honored Sir:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have received your honored letter and, therefore, send you<lb/>
                the <persName>Moses</persName> and <persName>Aaron</persName>* that you desired.
                    <persName>Holzman</persName>
                <sic>departedmfor</sic> the <placeName>West</placeName> 2<lb/> months ago. The
                wholesale price of the pictures is $.50 each. The<lb/> enclosed bill is being sent
                to you in order to show it to the customer<lb/> because I sell such at a retail
                price of $1. <persName>Mr. Moss</persName> will not come<lb/> until <date>Rosh
                    Hashonah</date>, and I shall write to him about the penitential<lb/> hymn-book
                for <date>Tish-a-b'av</date>. <persName>Mr. Bondi</persName> has until this moment
                not de-<lb/>livered anything masterful. The next issue will appear in a new
                shape<lb/> and is to bear the title, “Shomer Israel”. It is feared that he will
                lose<lb/> money, since the first issue contained over 130 typographical errors, i.
                e.<lb/> in the German article. Moreover, a new weekly is appearing here. If<lb/> you
                have a <hi rend="underline">free</hi> opportunity to have someone take something
                along, send<lb/> me 6 prayer books, “Dibrei Zaddikim”, in ordinary binding, because
                I hope<lb/> to do some more business for you before <date>Rosh Hashonah</date>. I
                shouldn't like<lb/> to pay for freight.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your most devoted friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Michael Light</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <placeName>94 East Broadway</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>* <persName>Moses</persName> and <persName>Aaron</persName> is the name of the two
                rollers upon which the Torah is<lb/> rolled.</p>
        </body>
